<2ND_LINE>BC-Italy-Pilots Strike,0122</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Italian Pilots Call Three-Day Strike</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Alitalia canceled 28 national and six international
flights Wednesday due to a strike by pilots.
   The pilots decided to strike for two hours each morning on
Wednesday, Thursday and Friday to protest the lack of progress in
contract talks between union representatives and the state airline.
   The airline said 44 national and 10 international flights would
be canceled Thursday. The number of cancellations for Friday was not
immediately known.
   Negotiations between the pilots and the airline revolve around
salary disputes.
   Air traffic controllers had called a strike for the same period,
but Transportation Minister Giorgio Santuz ordered those workers to
remain on the job.
</TEXT>
