<HEAD>Three Senior Executives Named to New Jobs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Tribune Co. has named Stanton R. Cook chairman
of the giant media company, a job that has been vacant for 14 years,
the company said today.
   Cook had been president and chief executive officer since 1974,
taking over when Harold F. Grumhaus retired.
   Cook, 63, will remain publisher of the Chicago Tribune newspaper.
   In other promotions announced Tuesday, Charles T. Brumback, 60,
will become president and chief operating officer of Tribune Co.,
the company said. Brumbach currently is president and chief
executive officer of Chicago Tribune Co., which produces and
distributes the newspaper.
   John W. Madigan, 51, will succeed Brumback as president and chief
executive officer of Chicago Tribune Co. Madigan also is executive
vice president of Tribune Co.
   Tribune Co. is a diversified media company engaged in newspaper
publishing, broadcasting, entertainment production and newsprint
manufacturing.
   In addition to the Chicago Tribune, it publishes the Orlando
Sentinel and the Daily News of New York, and operates WGN-TV.
   The appointments are effective Jan. 1.
