<TEXT>
   ConAgra Inc. officials said they will hold a
special meeting at the end of January or in early February to vote
on issuing up to 36.2 million shares of common stock in connection
with the proposed merger of Holly Farms Corp. and ConAgra.
   The two companies announced a definite merger agreement in
November. The boards of both companies have approved the agreement,
which is also subject to stockholder approval by both companies.
   To acquire Holly Farms, ConAgra of Omaha would issue up to 36.2
million shares of stock, worth about $1 billion.
   Tyson Foods sought a ruling Tuesday as part of its suit to
prevent the merger.
