<HEAD>Sprint Reduces Business Rates</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   US Sprint Communications Co. said Wednesday it
will reduce interstate rates for business products, including WATS
and 800 services, by an average of 3.6 percent on Jan. 5.
   The nation's third-largest long-distance carrier announced last
month that it will lower its basic interstate residential and
business rates on Jan. 1 by an average of 3.8 percent.
   The reductions reflect lower costs for connecting to the local
phone network. US Sprint's two larger rivals, American Telephone &
Telegraph Co. and MCI Communications Corp., recently announced price
cuts of 3.8 percent and 3.9 percent, respectively.
   US Sprint said the business products rate cut applies to Dial 1
WATS, Sprint Advanced WATS Plus, Sprint Advanced WATS, Banded WATS,
Ultra WATS, Virtual Private Network, Direct 800 and Ultra 800
services.
  
