<TEXT>
   CBS Inc. said Wednesday it tentatively had agreed
to buy two radio stations in Detroit, WWJ-AM and WJOI-FM.
   The stations are owned by Federal Broadcasting Co., a subsidiary
of Federal Enterprises Inc. which is based in Southfield, Mich.
   In a one-sentence statement, CBS said it had signed a non-binding
letter of intent to acquire WWJ-AM, a news and information station
that has been a CBS affiliate since 1975, and WJOI-FM, which uses an
