the telephone said there was no one available to comment on the
announcement.
   Federal Enterprises owns television stations in Marquette, Mich.,
and Kirksville, Mo., and a radio station in New York City.
   CBS owns 18 radio stations, including seven AM and 11 FM outlets.
Federal regulations permit a company to own up to 12 AM and 12 FM
radio stations.
