<HEAD>Ford Recalls California-Modified Escort, Lynx Models</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. is recalling 23,500 1985 and 1986
Ford Escort and Mercury Lynx models built for sale in California
because emissions levels could exceed state standards, the automaker
said Wednesday.
   The vehicles are equipped with 1.9-liter engines and manual or
automatic transmissions, Ford said in a statement.
   Owners of the vehicles will be notified by mail to take their
cars to dealerships, where repair work will be performed for free.
   Ford also said it would ask owners of about 200 vehicles built on
its 1987 diesel-powered E-350 Commercial Cutaway van platform to
return the vehicles to dealers to have the front springs replaced.
   Front springs now in the vehicles did not account for the added
weight of the diesel engine, the statement said.
