<1ST_LINE>u f AM-MacysLoss     12-14 0183</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Macys Loss,0189</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Macy's Reports $19 Million Loss in First Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   R.H. Macy & Co. on Wednesday reported a $19
million net loss in its first quarter ended Oct. 29, compared with a
net profit of $6.4 million a year earlier.
   The first-quarter loss occurred despite a 20 percent increase in
sales, to $1.62 billion from $1.35 billion.
   The New York Times, in Thursday's editions, attributed the loss
largely to erratic business and the pressure to stimulate sales by
cutting prices. As the retailer sells its goods at an increasingly
slim profit _ or even at a loss _ profits have dropped and in some
cases vanished, the Times said.
   Macy's, which has been privately held for about two years,
recently acquired two California fashion retailers, Bullock's and I.
Magnin. It is burdened with around $5.3 billion in debt from the
leveraged buyout by management that took it private and the
California acquisitions.
   For its fiscal year ended July 31, Macy's posted a net loss of
$134 million, of which $106 million was incurred in the fourth
quarter.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
